# recursive-spine — licence map

Different parts of this repository carry different licences, drawn
along the grain of what each part is for:

| Scope | Licence | Why |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `skills/`, `docs/`, `reference/`, `pollen/`, `README.md`, and all other prose | [CC BY 4.0](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/) | The method and its propagation primitives. Take them anywhere, adapt them, use them commercially — the credit line travels with every copy. |
| `scripts/`, `.github/` | [Apache-2.0](LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt) | Plumbing. |

**Attribution, in the manner we request (CC BY 4.0 §3(a)(1)):** one
line, wherever your copy or adaptation lives —

> Adapted from recursive-spine (https://github.com/slopstopper/recursive-spine),
> © 2026 Aoife Okonedo Martin, CC BY 4.0

Full licence texts: [LICENSES/](LICENSES/).

Using the plugin as a plugin — installing it, running its skills on
your repos, commercially or not — is use, not adaptation. It requires
nothing from you. These terms bind people who republish or repackage
the text; credit is the one thing that must survive the copy.
